| File | Lines | What Changed |
|------|-------|--------------|
| **`context/AuthContext.js`** | 9-20 | `syncTokenCookie` — added `Secure` flag (auto-applied on HTTPS) and documented that this is a legacy fallback; new API routes should use `createServerSupabase()`. |
| **`context/AuthContext.js`** | 73-99 | `recoverSession` — replaced `getSession()` (localStorage-only, can return stale/expired tokens) with `getUser()` as the primary validation call. `getUser()` validates the JWT against the Supabase server and triggers a token refresh when expired, eliminating the flash of incorrect auth state. |

