---

## Summary of Changes

### `context/AuthContext.js` — 3 fixes

| Lines | Function | Change |
|-------|----------|--------|
| 76-111 | `recoverSession` | **Fixed profile ordering**: moved `finishLoading()` out of the success path into the `finally` block only. Profile is now fetched and applied *before* loading completes, so `role`/`department`/`profile` are available when the page renders. Added a localStorage session fallback (lines 92-102) for offline scenarios where `getUser()` fails. |
| 123-125 | `onAuthStateChange` | **Fixed race condition**: added `if (event === 'INITIAL_SESSION') return;` — `recoverSession` handles initial load, so the listener no longer fires a competing concurrent profile fetch. |
| 163-178 | `logout` | **Enhanced session cleanup**: converted to `useCallback`, added `localStorage` cleanup that removes all `sb-*` keys (lines 171-174) so no stale Supabase tokens survive logout. |

### `components/TWAdminLayout.jsx` — 2 additions

| Lines | What | Change |
|-------|------|--------|
| 4, 25, 27-51 | Keyboard command | Added `useRef`/`useEffect` imports; destructured `logout` from `useAuth()`; added a `keydown` listener that tracks typed keys in a 6-char buffer with a 2-second inactivity reset — typing `logout` anywhere outside form fields triggers sign-out. |
| 89-94 | Logout button | Added a red `Logout` button in the admin header, next to "View Site", visible on all admin pages. Calls the same `logout()` from `useAuth()`. |

### Root Cause of Refresh Bug

`finishLoading()` was called on the line *before* `fetchUserProfile()`, so the page would render with `loading=false` + `user=<object>` but `profile=null`, `role=null`, `department=null`. Any component reading those values (like the role badge in the header) saw empty data until the `onAuthStateChange` listener independently re-fetched the profile — which itself raced with the recovery function.

[2026-04-07T21:57:51.023Z] KNOXIS (review): Claude has finished investigating and implementing the fixes. The main issues were with the `recoverSession` function in `context/AuthContext.js`, where the profile ordering was incorrect, and a race condition in `onAuthStateChange`. These have been fixed, and a logout feature has been added, including a button and a keyboard command. The logout function now properly cleans up the session and removes all Supabase tokens from local storage. The root cause of the refresh bug was identified as a premature call to `finishLoading()` before the user profile was fetched, which has been corrected. You can now test the application to see if the issues are resolved.
